Package: bairrtt
Type: Package
Title: Causal Inference with a Latent IRT Confounder via BART and WALNUTS
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Vincent", "Dorie", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           email = "vincent.dorie@georgetown.edu"),
    person("Bob", "Carpenter", role = c("ctb", "cph"),
           comment = "author of the bundled WALNUTS C++ headers (inst/include/walnuts)"))
Description: Fits a causal model in which a latent person trait, measured by a
    two-parameter logistic (2PL) item-response model, acts as a confounder
    between a binary treatment and a continuous outcome. Two Bayesian Additive
    Regression Trees (BART) surfaces (from 'dbarts') model the outcome and the
    treatment assignment as flexible functions of the latent trait; the IRT item
    parameters are drawn conditional on the trait by the gradient-based WALNUTS
    sampler (a No-U-Turn variant), and the trait itself by per-person
    Metropolis. The Gibbs sampler is exposed as a single entry point that runs on
    an arbitrary item-response matrix, and the WALNUTS item-parameter sampler is
    exported for reuse.
